    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7291646b_11f9f9fd",
        "filename": "util/linux/memory_map_test.cc",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 271,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-04-24T14:44:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I disagree. We don’t want gratuitous delays in tests. One second is actually a really long time. It’s pretty bad if every test slept for a second, and this sleep makes it a real pain to run this test in a tight --gtest_repeat loop.\n\nYou can do this with a sleep that’s way, way shorter than a second.",
      "revId": "bf45ada33a432caf27bc795e6b55a10ca7cd9b70",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "7ee5ce54_4823783e",
        "filename": "util/linux/memory_map_test.cc",
        "patchSetId": 11
      },
      "lineNbr": 281,
      "author": {
        "id": 1174099
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-04-24T14:44:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "EXPECT_EQ(kill(…), 0) \u003c\u003c ErrnoMessage(\"kill\");\n\nbut I think we’d generally prefer to get rid of this (and line 265) altogether and let the child process die naturally when it recognizes that the parent no longer cares about it. (See below.)",
      "revId": "bf45ada33a432caf27bc795e6b55a10ca7cd9b70",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
